"03_behavior.mst — Behavior/Class/Metaclass (sprint_s06_detail.md #03).
 instVarAt: indices follow oops/layout.rs's KLASS_*_INDEX order, 1-based:
 1 format, 2 non_indexable_size, 3 superclass, 4 methods, 5 name,
 6 inst_var_names, 7 class_vars, 8 mixin."

"I am the abstract superclass of Class and Metaclass — the objects that
 describe other objects. I know my name, superclass and instVarNames, I
 make instances with new and new: (for indexable classes), and I answer
 inheritance questions with inheritsFrom:. Every object reaches me
 through its class, e.g. anObject class name."

Object subclass: Behavior [
    name [
        ^self instVarAt: 5
    ]
    superclass [
        ^self instVarAt: 3
    ]
    instVarNames [
        ^self instVarAt: 6
    ]
    new [
        ^self basicNew
    ]
    new: n [
        ^self basicNew: n
    ]
    inheritsFrom: aClass [
        | s |
        s := self superclass.
        [ s notNil ] whileTrue: [
            s == aClass ifTrue: [ ^true ].
            s := s superclass ].
        ^false
    ]
]

"I represent an ordinary class: Object, String and every class you
 define are my instances. All of my useful behavior — name, superclass,
 new, new:, inheritsFrom: — is inherited from Behavior; I exist so that
 classes proper can be told apart from metaclasses."

Behavior subclass: Class [
]

"I represent the class of a class. Each class has its own metaclass,
 which holds its class-side methods (those defined with ClassName class
 >> selector). Like Class, everything I actually do is inherited from
 Behavior."

Behavior subclass: Metaclass [
]

nil subclass: Object [
    isKindOf: aClass [
        ^self class == aClass or: [ self class inheritsFrom: aClass ]
    ]
    isMemberOf: aClass [
        ^self class == aClass
    ]
]
